text: Franklin County is a county in the state of Maine, in the United States. As of the 2020 census, the population was 29,456, making it the second-least populous county in Maine. The county seat is Farmington. The county was founded on May 9, 1838 and named for Benjamin Franklin. == References == Category:19th-century establishments in Maine Category:1838 establishments in the United States Category:Maine counties
title: Franklin County, Maine
